Tata Consultancy Tax Payment Likely to Double, Official Says

-- B y   A n o o p   A g r a w a l
-- 
2011-09-15T06:48:24Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-15/tata-consultancy-s-tax-payment-likely-to-double-official-says.html
Tata Consultancy Services Ltd. (TCS) ’s
tax payment for the three months ending Sept. 30 may double to
5.7 billion rupees, an official in Mumbai’s tax department said.  Tata Steel Ltd. (TATA) , India’s biggest producer, may pay 6.2
billion rupees in tax, the official said, declining to be
identified because of department rules.  Companies pay tax in advance based on their estimated
income for the year, the official said.  Larsen & Toubro Ltd. (LT)  is
likely to pay 3.5 billion rupees, while  Bank of Baroda (BOB)  will pay
6.3 billion rupees, the official said.  Advance tax payments are monitored by investors as an
indicator of profitability.  Tata Consultancy shares advanced 0.9 percent to 1,024.55
rupees as of 12:16 p.m. in Mumbai, a third day of gains.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Anoop Agrawal in Mumbai at 
